Yidongfang Si  司懿东方  

y_si@mit.edu  |  Curriculum Vitae


I'm a Postdoc at MIT, working with Prof. Abigail Bodner on submesoscale ocean dynamics. My research interests lie broadly in geophysical fluid dynamics, turbulence, ice-ocean interactions, eddies, and tides. 


Previously, I worked with Prof. Raffaele Ferrari at MIT on ocean bottom boundary layers. I received my Ph.D. from UCLA, where I worked on ice-ocean interactions under the supervision of Prof. Andrew Stewart. I earned my B.S. from Peking University, where I studied ocean circulation on exoplanets.

Employment:

  • Jul 2025 – Present, Postdoctoral Associate, Massachusetts Institute of Technology

  • Jun 2023 – Jun 2025, Houghton Postdoctoral Fellow, Massachusetts Institute of Technology

Education:

  • Sep 2018 – Jun 2023, Ph.D. in Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences, University of California, Los Angeles 

  • Sep 2014 – Jul 2018, B.S. in Astronomy, School of Physics, Peking University
